{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before the VM boots, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiskInjector"},{"type":"text","text":" mounts the guest disk image on the host,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"writes a standard macOS LaunchDaemon plist and the user’s script to the data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"volume, then unmounts. When the VM boots, "},{"code":"launchd","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" picks up the daemon and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"executes the script automatically — no SSH, no agent, no network required."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This uses Apple’s "},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (ships with macOS) to attach APFS disk images"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and writes only to the data volume (never the Signed System Volume)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Usage","text":"Usage","level":2},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let scriptURL = URL(fileURLWithPath: \"\/path\/to\/setup.sh\")","let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","try DiskInjector.inject(script: scriptURL, into: bundle)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"How-It-Works","text":"How It Works"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Attaches the guest’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"disk.img"},{"type":"text","text":" using "},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" without mounting"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(to discover the device node).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finds and mounts the APFS data volume from the attached disk."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes the user’s script to "},{"code":"\/usr\/local\/bin\/spooktacular-user-data.sh","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the data volume."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes a LaunchDaemon plist to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/Library\/LaunchDaemons\/"},{"type":"text","text":" that tells"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"launchd"},{"type":"text","text":" to run the script at boot."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Detaches the disk image so the VM can boot cleanly.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Thread-Safety","text":"Thread Safety","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are synchronous and use "},{"code":"Process","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to invoke "},{"code":"hdiutil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Call from a background thread if needed to avoid blocking the main thread."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/diskinjector"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Injects a user-data script into a VM’s guest disk as a macOS LaunchDaemon."}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit12DiskInjectorO","symbolKind":"enum","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"